{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2008w","heading":"Rural Innovation Stronger Economy Grant Program","label":"2008w Rural Innovation Stronger Economy Grant Program","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/ch50/schIV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe Rural Electrification Act of 1936, referred to in subsec. (a)(1)(B)(ii)(III)(bb), is , . Title VI of the Act is classified generally to subchapter VI (§ 950bb et seq.) of chapter 31 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see and Tables.act May 20, 1936, ch. 43249 Stat. 1363section 901 of this title"],"amendments":["References in TextThe Rural Electrification Act of 1936, referred to in subsec. (a)(1)(B)(ii)(III)(bb), is , . Title VI of the Act is classified generally to subchapter VI (§ 950bb et seq.) of chapter 31 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see and Tables.act May 20, 1936, ch. 43249 Stat. 1363section 901 of this title"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Definitions","label":"a Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Eligible entity","label":"1 Eligible entity","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"focuses on the shared goals and needs of the industry clusters that are objectively identified as existing, emerging, or declining;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"represents a region defined by the partnership in accordance with subparagraph (B);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iii/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fiii%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an institution of higher education (as defined in );section 1001 of title 20","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iii/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fiii%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a private entity; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"III","heading":null,"label":"III","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iii/III","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fiii%2FIII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a government entity; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iv/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iv","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fiv%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a District Organization (as defined in section 300.3 of title 13, Code of Federal Regulations (or a successor regulation));","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iv/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iv","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fiv%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an Indian tribe (as defined in ), or a consortium of Indian tribes;section 5304 of title 25","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"III","heading":null,"label":"III","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iv/III","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iv","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fiv%2FIII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a State or a political subdivision of a State, including a special purpose unit of a State or local government engaged in economic development activities, or a consortium of political subdivisions;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"IV","heading":null,"label":"IV","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iv/IV","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iv","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fiv%2FIV","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an institution of higher education (as defined in ) or a consortium of institutions of higher education; orsection 1001 of title 20","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"V","heading":null,"label":"V","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iv/V","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/A/iv","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FA%2Fiv%2FV","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a public or private nonprofit organization; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/i/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fi%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a single jurisdiction; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/i/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fi%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"if the region is a rural area, multijurisdictional; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fii%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is large enough to contain critical elements of the industry cluster prioritized by the partnership;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fii%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is small enough to enable close collaboration among members of the partnership;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"III","heading":null,"label":"III","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii/III","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fii%2FIII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"item","nativeType":"item","number":"aa","heading":null,"label":"aa","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii/III/aa","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii/III","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fii%2FIII%2Faa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a nonmetropolitan area that qualifies as a low-income community (as defined in ); andsection 45D(e) of title 26","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"item","nativeType":"item","number":"bb","heading":null,"label":"bb","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii/III/bb","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii/III","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fii%2FIII%2Fbb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an area that has access to or has a plan to achieve broadband service (within the meaning of title VI of the Rural Electrification Act of 1936 ( et seq.)); and7 U.S.C. 950bb","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"IV","heading":null,"label":"IV","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii/IV","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fii%2FIV","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"item","nativeType":"item","number":"aa","heading":null,"label":"aa","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii/IV/aa","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii/IV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fii%2FIV%2Faa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has a population of 50,000 or fewer inhabitants; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"item","nativeType":"item","number":"bb","heading":null,"label":"bb","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii/IV/bb","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/1/B/ii/IV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fii%2FIV%2Fbb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for a region with a population of more than 50,000 inhabitants, is the subject of a positive determination by the Secretary with respect to a rural-in-character petition, including such a petition submitted concurrently with the application of the partnership for a grant under this section.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Industry cluster","label":"2 Industry cluster","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “industry cluster” means a broadly defined network of interconnected firms and supporting institutions in related industries that accelerate innovation, business formation, and job creation by taking advantage of assets and strengths of a region in the business environment.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"High-wage job","label":"3 High-wage job","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “high-wage job” means a job that provides a wage that is greater than the median wage for the applicable region, as determined by the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Jobs accelerator","label":"4 Jobs accelerator","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “jobs accelerator” means a jobs accelerator center or program located in or serving a low-income rural community that may provide co-working space, in-demand skills training, entrepreneurship support, and any other services described in subsection (d)(1)(B).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":"Small and disadvantaged business","label":"5 Small and disadvantaged business","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fa%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “small and disadvantaged business” has the meaning given the term “small business concern owned and controlled by socially and economically disadvantaged individuals” in .section 637(d)(3)(C) of title 15","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Establishment","label":"b Establishment","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"improve the ability of distressed rural communities to create high-wage jobs, accelerate the formation of new businesses with high-growth potential, and strengthen regional economies, including by helping to build capacity in the applicable region to achieve those goals; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"help rural communities identify and maximize local assets and connect to regional opportunities, networks, and industry clusters that demonstrate high growth potential.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Cost-sharing","label":"2 Cost-sharing","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Federal share of the cost of any activity carried out using a grant made under paragraph (1) shall be not greater than 80 percent.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"In-kind contributions","label":"B In-kind contributions","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The non-Federal share of the total cost of any activity carried out using a grant made under paragraph (1) may be in the form of donations or in-kind contributions of goods or services fairly valued.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Selection criteria","label":"3 Selection criteria","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F3%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"investment organizations, including venture development organizations, venture capital firms, revolving loan funders, angel investment groups, community lenders, community development financial institutions, rural business investment companies, small business investment companies (as defined in ), philanthropic organizations, and other institutions focused on expanding access to capital, are committed partners in the jobs accelerator partnership and willing to potentially invest in projects emerging from the jobs accelerator; andsection 662 of title 15","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F3%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"institutions of higher education, applied research institutions, workforce development entities, and community-based organizations are willing to partner with the jobs accelerator to provide workers with skills relevant to the industry cluster needs of the region, with an emphasis on the use of on-the-job training, registered apprenticeships, customized training, classroom occupational training, or incumbent worker training;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the ability of the eligible entity to provide the non-Federal share as required under paragraph (2);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F3%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the identification of a targeted industry cluster;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F3%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the ability of the partnership to link rural communities to markets, networks, industry clusters, and other regional opportunities and assets;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F3%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"other grants or loans of the Secretary and other Federal agencies that the jobs accelerator would be able to leverage; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"F","heading":null,"label":"F","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3/F","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F3%2FF","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"prospects for the proposed center and related programming to have sustainability beyond the full maximum length of assistance under this subsection, including the maximum number of renewals.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Grant term and renewals","label":"4 Grant term and renewals","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"Term","label":"A Term","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/4/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F4%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The initial term of a grant under paragraph (1) shall be 4 years.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Renewal","label":"B Renewal","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/4/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F4%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary may extend the term of a grant under paragraph (1) for an additional period of not longer than 2 years if the Secretary is satisfied, using the evaluation under subsection (e)(2), that the grant recipient has successfully established a jobs accelerator and related programming.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":"Geographic distribution","label":"5 Geographic distribution","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fb%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To the maximum extent practicable, the Secretary shall provide grants under paragraph (1) for jobs accelerators and related programming in not fewer than 25 States at any time.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Grant amount","label":"c Grant amount","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"not less than $500,000; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"not more than $2,000,000.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Use of funds","label":"d Use of funds","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to construct, purchase, or equip a building to serve as an innovation center;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"linking rural communities and entrepreneurs to markets, networks, industry clusters, and other regional opportunities to support high-wage job creation, new business formation, business expansion, and economic growth;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"integrating small businesses into a supply chain;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1%2FB%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"creating or expanding commercialization activities for new business formation;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1%2FB%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"identifying and building assets in rural communities that are crucial to supporting regional economies;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"v","heading":null,"label":"v","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B/v","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1%2FB%2Fv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"facilitating the repatriation of high-wage jobs to the United States;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"vi","heading":null,"label":"vi","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B/vi","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1%2FB%2Fvi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"supporting the deployment of innovative processes, technologies, and products;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"vii","heading":null,"label":"vii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B/vii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1%2FB%2Fvii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"enhancing the capacity of small businesses in regional industry clusters, including small and disadvantaged businesses;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"viii","heading":null,"label":"viii","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B/viii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1%2FB%2Fviii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"increasing United States exports and business interaction with international buyers and suppliers;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ix","heading":null,"label":"ix","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B/ix","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1%2FB%2Fix","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"developing the skills and expertise of local workforces, entrepreneurs, and institutional partners to meet the needs of employers and prepare workers for high-wage jobs in the identified industry clusters, including the upskilling of incumbent workers;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"x","heading":null,"label":"x","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B/x","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1%2FB%2Fx","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"ensuring rural communities have the capacity and ability to carry out projects relating to housing, community facilities, infrastructure, or community and economic development to support regional industry cluster growth; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"xi","heading":null,"label":"xi","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B/xi","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F1%2FB%2Fxi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any other activities that the Secretary may determine to be appropriate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Requirement","label":"2 Requirement","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Subject to subparagraph (B), not more than 10 percent of a grant awarded under subsection (b) shall be used for indirect costs associated with administering the grant.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Increase","label":"B Increase","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft7%2Fs2008w%2Fd%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary may increase the percentage described in subparagraph (A) on a case-by-case basis.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":"Annual activity report and evaluation","label":"e Annual activity report and evaluation","identifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t7/s2008w","sourceUrl":"https://